/*the 3rd set of style:   border-bottom: 30px solid #cccccc; will apply to all elements with .intro (i.e. p.intro, ul.intro)
If there's conflict between p.intro and .intro, the p.intro styling will take precedence.

another situation:
if both p.intro and .intro have !important, p.intro takes precedence b/c it's more specific.*/

p.intro {
          font-size: 30px;
          background-color: green !important;
        }

ul.intro {
          background-color: blue;
      }   

.intro {
        border-bottom: 30px solid #cccccc;
        background-color: yellow !important;
}

